    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI want to use `gO` to see table of contents (TOC) of checkhealth buffer, and then move to the session I want using that TOC. However, when the table of contents (which is also a loclist) is opened, the checkhealth buffer is also removed, which means the TOC is now useless.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. nvim --clean -c \"lua vim.g.health = { style = 'float' }\"\n2. `:checkhealth`\n3. Type `gO`\n4. Press enter in the loclist to go to a session you want \n => E92: Bufffer 2 not found\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe checkhealth window should remains opened when I open its TOC\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-cbfc3d1cdc\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNA\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nKubuntu 24.04.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkonsole\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nSource",
