            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Starting `nvim -c 'au VimEnter * source test.vim'` with the following `test.vim`, then typing `gO`, the problem *doesn't* happen:\n\n```\nhelp\nlua vim.g.mywin = vim.api.nvim_open_win(0, false, {relative='editor',width=80,height=6,row=6,col=6,zindex=2})\nclose\nwincmd w\n```\n\n\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/34794 explains why it happens for checkheatlh:\n\n> because LSP floating preview system auto-closes on BufEnter events triggered by :lopen.\n\n",
